    content:
      'The graph below shows the results of an experiment conducted by a team of researchers investigating the relationship between the composition and melting point of different DNA samples. At the melting point, the DNA double helix separates into two individual strands.\nTwo DNA samples were compared, one consisting of only PQ pairs and another one consisting of only RS pairs.  Letters P, Q, R and S represent different nitrogenous bases found in the DNA.\n![SkillUpp Image](https://assets.revisionvillage.com/public/question/d59dd324-98c9-4e4e-91b6-758d5679701c/images/0881eea3-e69e-45cc-ad3b-7c9e377763b5/BI0321.png)\n\n\r\n[ © Revision Village 2022]\n\nBased on the results presented in the graph, and your knowledge of nucleotide base pairing (between purines and pyrimidines), deduce which nitrogenous bases correspond to the letters P, Q, R and S.\n P  Q  R  S  A. $\\hspace{1.5em}$CytosineGuanineThymineAdenine$\\hspace{1.5em}$ B. $\\hspace{1.5em}$AdenineCytosineGuanineThymine$\\hspace{1.5em}$ C. $\\hspace{1.5em}$GuanineAdenineThymineCytosine$\\hspace{1.5em}$ D. $\\hspace{1.5em}$ThymineAdenineCytosineGuanine',
