      'Marbled crayfish, Procambarus virginalis (shown below) only reproduce through parthenogenesis, a type of asexual reproduction.\n\n![SkillUpp Image](https://assets.revisionvillage.com/public/question/ba0e6004-4d7f-48a7-bf9e-a8069777b737/images/c8f8303c-ea98-4db3-beb6-4205e32b355a/BI2655.png)\n\n\n[Adapted from Lyko, F. (2017). The marbled crayfish (Decapoda: Cambaridae) represents an independent new species. Zootaxa 4363(4): 544–552. Retrieved 10/03/2025, DOI: 10.11646/zootaxa.4363.4.6. CC PY]\n\nWhich of the following statements about classifying these crayfish is/are correct?\n\n\n- I.They produce genetically identical offspring, making species classification impossibleII.They cannot be classified using the biological species conceptIII.They can produce many offspring so cannot be classified using the biological species concept\n\n\n\n\n- A.$\\hspace{1em}$ II only\n- B.$\\hspace{1em}$ II and III\n- C.$\\hspace{1em}$ I and II\n- D.$\\hspace{1em}$ I, II, and III\n',
