      'The following table shows the approximate number of protein-encoding genes found in various species. What can be concluded from these findings?\nSpeciesApproximate number of protein-encoding genesDrosophila melanogaster (fruit fly)14,000Oryza sativa (rice)51,000Gallus gallus (chicken)20,000-23,000Homo sapiens (human)20,000-25,000\n\n\n- I.The number of genes is not a good indicator of organism complexity.II.Chickens may have more genes than humans.III.The number of base pairs in the rice genome is greater than in the other species.\n\n\n\n\n- A.$\\hspace{1em}$ I and II only\n- B.$\\hspace{1em}$ II and III only\n- C.$\\hspace{1em}$ I and III only\n- D.$\\hspace{1em}$ I, II and III\n',
