      'The image shows changes in coverage to mixed dipterocarp forests in Southeast Asia over the last 100 years.\nWhich is not a factor that contributed to these changes?\n![SkillUpp Image](https://assets.revisionvillage.com/public/question/a1fefead-ab2a-4ce6-991b-34aa2eb33cde/images/ede73a61-24fa-43b8-b1ae-1135b7e67858/BI0904_A4.2.png)\n\n\n[Source: Adapted from San Jose. (2006, February 8). File: map of east asia.png - wikimedia commons. Wikimedia commons. Retrieved July 10, 2023 from URL https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File: Map_of_East_Asia.png. Copyright under CC BY 3.0]\n\n\n\n- A.$\\hspace{1em}$ Building of new roads to mining sites\n- B.$\\hspace{1em}$ Poaching of endangered species\n- C.$\\hspace{1em}$ Planting of rubber plantations\n- D.$\\hspace{1em}$ Building of hydroelectric dams\n',
