      'Which approach, carried out by conservationists in zoos and botanical gardens, defines the transition between ex-situ conservation and in-situ conservation?\n\n\n\n- A.$\\hspace{1em}$ Building more capacity in zoos and botanical gardens.\n- B.$\\hspace{1em}$ Carrying out artificial selection within zoos and botanical gardens.\n- C.$\\hspace{1em}$ Building the population of captive-bred species across zoos and botanical gardens in many countries.\n- D.$\\hspace{1em}$ Release of captive-bred species from zoos and botanical gardens into nature reserves.\n',
