    markScheme:
      'B\n\n$\\underline{\\textrm{Explanation}}$: \nAdenine and guanine are purines. Cytosine and thymine are pyrimidines.\nIf S is a pyrimidine (~20%), it is either cytosine or thymine. Purines pair with pyrimidines, so Q, which also makes up about 20% of the molecule, must be guanine or adenine. This means Choices A and D can be eliminated as correct answers.\nP and R must pair up as they make up approximately the same proportion of the DNA. So P and R must either be adenine and thymine or guanine and cytosine. This means Choice C is incorrect.\nThis leaves us with the correct answer of Choice B.  P is guanine, which pairs with R, cytosine, and Q is adenine, which pairs with S, which must be thymine.',
