      'The micrograph below shows Cyanobacteria, which contain chlorophyll.\n![SkillUpp Image](https://assets.revisionvillage.com/public/question/c3dfa29a-d486-40b4-9fc1-d44b66ce3fc7/images/937853fc-bf32-495b-aba7-33e0cf82a199/BI1197-SL.png)\n\n\n[Source: Adapted from Thompson L. and Whatson N. (2007, January 1).  Cyanobacteria.  Wikipedia.  Retrieved on September 6, 2023, from https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyanobacteria#. Copyright under CCO]\n\n- Using your knowledge and the micrograph, state two features that would indicate that this is a bacterium.\t <span class="marks">[2]</span>\n\n- Outline the structural differences between animal and plant cells.  <span class="marks">[3]</span>\n\n- Explain how light energy is used in photosynthesis to carry out anabolic reactions. <span class="marks">[3]</span>\n\n',
    markScheme:
      '\n- Any two of the following\n  $\\ce{ -> }$ cell wall of peptidoglycan\t\t\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n  $\\ce{ -> }$ naked DNA OR DNA not associated with histones OR proteins\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n  $\\ce{ -> }$ nucleoid OR DNA free in cytoplasm\t\t\t\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n  $\\ce{ -> }$ no membrane bound organelles\t\t\t\t\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n  $\\ce{ -> }$ 70s ribosomes\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n  $\\ce{ -> }$ cell smaller than 10μm\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n<span class="marks">[<strong>2 marks maximum</strong>]</span>\n\n  $\\underline{\\textrm{Sample answer}}$: \nTwo features that would indicate that this is a bacterium are it has no membrane-bound organelles ($\\checkmark$) and 70s ribosomes ($\\checkmark$).\n\n\n\n- Any three of the following:\n  $\\ce{ -> }$ plant cells have a cell wall, WHEREAS animal cells do not\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n  $\\ce{ -> }$ plant cells generally have a central vacuole WHEREAS animal cells do not\t\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n  $\\ce{ -> }$ plant cells have chloroplasts WHEREAS animal cells do not\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n  $\\ce{ -> }$ animal cells may have lysosomes WHEREAS plant cells do not\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n  $\\ce{ -> }$ animal cells may have cilia OR flagella WHEREAS plant cells do not\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n  $\\ce{ -> }$ animal cells have centrioles WHEREAS plant cells do not\t\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n<span class="marks">[<strong>3 marks maximum</strong>]</span>\n\n  $\\underline{\\textrm{Sample answer}}$: \nPlant cells have a cell wall, central vacuole and chloroplasts, whereas animal cells do not ($\\checkmark$) ($\\checkmark$) ($\\checkmark$).\n\n\n\n- Any three of the following:\n  $\\ce{ -> }$ light energy is absorbed by chlorophyll\t\t\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n  $\\ce{ -> }$ light energy is transferred to electrons OR is used to excite electrons\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n  $\\ce{ -> }$ light energy splitting water molecules OR photolysis releases electrons for the electron transport chain OR hydrogen ions for use in ATP production\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n  $\\ce{ -> }$ light energy is used to synthesise ATP from ADP and inorganic phosphate OR NADPH from electrons and one proton\t\t\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n  $\\ce{ -> }$ NADPH OR ATP is used to make larger organic compounds OR glucose OR starch OR other named organic compound from carbon dioxide\t\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n<span class="marks">[<strong>3 marks maximum</strong>]</span>\n\n  $\\underline{\\textrm{Sample answer}}$: \nLight energy is absorbed by chlorophyll ($\\checkmark$) and is used to excite electrons ($\\checkmark$).  These electrons reduce NADP+ to form NADPH, which is an anabolic reaction ($\\checkmark$).  Energy present in NADPH is then used to produce glucose from carbon dioxide ($\\checkmark$).  This is also an anabolic reaction.\n',
