      'Below is a diagram of Saccharomyces cervesiae commonly referred to as Brewer\'s yeast.\n![SkillUpp Image](https://assets.revisionvillage.com/public/question/d48038b1-43cc-4f2a-a666-47ce7e1443d1/images/42c78d0e-6ccf-4251-81a8-22cd1b96d088/BI2438.png)\n\n\n[© RevisionVillage2025. Created with BioRender.com]\n\n\n- Distinguish between the cell wall in fungal and plant cells.\t\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n- \n  - Explain the presence of chloroplast in plant cells, but not animal or fungal cells.  <span class="marks">[2]</span>\n\n  - A chloroplast is a type of plastid. Outline the function of one other named type of plastid found in plant cells that is absent in fungal cells. \t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n\n',
