      'The diagram depicts a single-celled organism living in freshwater that faces water constantly moving into its cell due to osmosis.\n![SkillUpp Image](https://assets.revisionvillage.com/public/question/e5d92e73-ab20-43da-aee4-b427dbf75796/images/c2bb4cec-e54b-4a2c-8f44-13ddf6b20f8d/BI2792.png)\n\n\n[Source: Adapted from File: Paramecium caudatum.svg. (2024, March 12). Wikimedia Commons. Retrieved 04:34, April 23, 2025 from https://commons.wikimedia.org/w/index.php?title=File.svg&oldid=859786930.CC Public Domain]\n\nTo prevent bursting, the cell actively pumps out excess water using specialised structures. This process is an example of:\n\n\n\n- A.$\\hspace{1em}$ Obtaining nutrients\n- B.$\\hspace{1em}$ Eliminating waste products\n- C.$\\hspace{1em}$ Responding to external stimuli\n- D.$\\hspace{1em}$ Maintaining homeostasis\n',
