    content:
      'The micrograph shows an image of a plant cell taken with a light microscope.\n![SkillUpp Image](https://assets.revisionvillage.com/public/question/529d9d46-e561-4668-8935-82e7109e4e46/images/6f5e50c0-57d2-40c7-974e-cc3073202c83/BI0816A.png)\n\n\n[Source: Adapted from CNX OpenStax. (2016, May 27). File 04 00 00new.jpg. Wikimedia commons. Retrieved June 14, 2023, from https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File: Figure_04_00_00new.jpg . Copyright free]\n\n- Calculate the magnification of the image, showing your work.\t<span class="marks">[2]</span>\n\n- Label, with the letter N, a nucleus in the image.\t<span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n- The image was taken using a light microscope. State how you deduce this from the image. <span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n- Draw and label a diagram to show how the same type of plant cell shown in the micrograph would appear when examined with an electron microscope.\t\t<span class="marks">[3]</span>\n\n- State two differences that would be seen when looking at an electron micrograph of a bacterium cell compared to this plant cell.\t\t<span class="marks">[2]</span>\n\n- At first, the student who took this image could not see the cell when focusing the microscope.  Suggest what may have caused this problem. <span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n',
