      'Ammophila arenaria (Marram grass), pictured below, is plant species that is often found on sand dunes.\n![SkillUpp Image](https://assets.revisionvillage.com/public/question/e59ef338-b88a-4ced-96ef-1826cfcd2025/images/30736373-9328-49f9-95e6-c476e1a892d2/BI1021A.png)\n\n\n[Source: Agnieszka K., Nova. (2020). File: Ammophila arenaria Piaskownica zwyczajna 2020-06-29 04.jpg\n.Wikimediacommons. Retrieved July 29, 2023, from https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File: Ammophila_arenaria_Piaskownica_zwyczajna_2020-06-29_04.jpg.  Copyright under CC BY-SA 4.0\n]\n\n- \n  - Identify the genus to which Ammophila arenaria belongs. <span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n  - State the naming system used to name Ammophila arenaria. <span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n  - State the term used to describe the differences between organisms, which is used as the basis for the naming system in part (ii).  <span class="marks">[1]</span>\n\n  - Describe how the genome within a species could vary.\t <span class="marks">[2]</span>\n\n\n- Compare and contrast the morphological and biological species concepts. \t<span class="marks">[2]</span>\n\n',
