      'Which of the following statements accurately describes characteristics of homologous structures?\n\n\n- I.Homologous structures are defined as functionally similar anatomical features that arise through divergent evolution.II.Although bats and dolphins exhibit distinct external morphology, their forelimbs evolved from a common ancestor.III.Bird wings and insect wings originate from the same embryonic tissues and are therefore homologous.\n\n\n\n\n- A.$\\hspace{1em}$ I only\n- B.$\\hspace{1em}$ II only\n- C.$\\hspace{1em}$ II and III only\n- D.$\\hspace{1em}$ I, II and III\n',
