      '\n- Outline why scientists must have several approaches to conserve biodiversity.   <span class="marks">[3]</span>\n\n- There are approximately 80 Javan Rhinoceros (Rhinoceros sondaicus) in the world. Discuss the environmental and economic implications the Indonesian government must consider before volunteering the Javan Rhinoceros to the EDGE programme.        <span class="marks">[5]</span>\n\n- Explain why rapid human population growth is linked to the current biodiversity crisis.   <span class="marks">[7]</span>\n\n',
